      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Beat the egg in a baking dish or pie plate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Whisk in the melted butter, then slowly add the milk and vanilla, whisking to combine."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the sugar, salt, flour and spices (optional) while continuing to whisk until totally smooth."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Soak each side of the bread in the batter for about 15-20 seconds."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat a skillet or griddle over medium heat and spread butter all over the bottom. I just hold a stick and rub it everywhere."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cook the bread for about 1 minute, or until golden and flip the bread, cooking on the other side for equal time or until golden."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Serve with maple syrup, crispy bacon, mascarpone cheese and fresh fruit (bananas, strawberries)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Pancakes are tough or chewy",
              "cause": "Over-mixed batter — gluten developed.",
              "fix": "Mix until just combined; lumps are fine. Rest the batter 10 minutes before cooking."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Pancakes are flat, not fluffy",
              "cause": "Baking powder stale, or butter too cool.",
              "fix": "Use fresh raising agents and melted butter, not cold. Don't flatten when flipping."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Stuck to the pan",
              "cause": "Pan not hot enough, or not enough fat.",
              "fix": "Medium heat, butter or oil swirled before each pancake. Wait until bubbles appear on top before flipping."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Cooked unevenly — pale in the middle, dark at the edges",
              "cause": "Pan too hot.",
              "fix": "Drop the heat. Cook longer per side at lower temperature for a more even brown."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sweet: serve with maple syrup, lemon and sugar, or fresh berries and yoghurt."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Savoury: skip the sugar in the batter; top with smoked salmon, cream cheese, and chives."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Classical French cookery rests on this kind of dish — slow extraction, considered seasoning, restraint at the finish. Escoffier and the Larousse Gastronomique codified the method; cooks like Elizabeth David and Julia Child brought it into the English-language kitchen."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
